UBS Group AG Has $826,000 Position in China Telecom Corp Ltd (CHA)


					Posted by Charlotte Bryant on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




UBS Group AG boosted its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp Ltd (NYSE:CHA) by 38.4% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 16,974 shares of the utilities provider’s stock after buying an additional 4,713 shares during the period. UBS Group AG’s holdings in China Telecom Corp were worth $826,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other large investors have also recently bought and sold shares of CHA. World Asset Management Inc raised its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp by 1.0% in the first quarter. World Asset Management Inc now owns 8,644 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $421,000 after buying an additional 83 shares in the last quarter.  Comerica Bank raised its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp by 1.3% in the first quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 7,956 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $392,000 after buying an additional 104 shares in the last quarter.  Bank of Montreal Can raised its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp by 1.5% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 7,545 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $367,000 after buying an additional 108 shares in the last quarter.  Wells Fargo & Company MN raised its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp by 4.5% in the first quarter. Wells Fargo & Company MN now owns 8,040 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $391,000 after buying an additional 349 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Capstone Asset Management Co. raised its position in shares of  China Telecom Corp by 6.6% in the first quarter. Capstone Asset Management Co. now owns 10,305 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $502,000 after buying an additional 640 shares in the last quarter. 0.43% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 


 Get China Telecom Corp Ltd alerts:



China Telecom Corp Ltd (NYSE:CHA) opened at 48.34 on Friday. The company’s 50-day moving average is $48.26 and its 200 day moving average is $48.35. The company has a market capitalization of $39.12 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 14.65 and a beta of 0.66. China Telecom Corp Ltd has a 52 week low of $45.58 and a 52 week high of $53.87. 





TRADEMARK VIOLATION WARNING: “UBS Group AG Has $826,000 Position in China Telecom Corp Ltd (CHA)” was first  published by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this story on another website, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of US and international copyright legislation. The correct version of this story can be accessed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/22/ubs-group-ag-has-826000-position-in-china-telecom-corp-ltd-cha.html. 
Several brokerages recently issued reports on CHA. BidaskClub lowered shares of China Telecom Corp from a “sell” rating to a “strong sell” rating in a research note on Thursday, June 22nd. Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of China Telecom Corp from a “strong-buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Tuesday, May 23rd. One investment analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating, six have issued  a buy rating and one  has given a strong buy rating to the company. The stock  has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average price target of $54.00.
China Telecom Corp Company Profile
China Telecom Corporation Limited is an investment holding company principally engaged in telecommunications and related businesses. The Company operates through seven businesses. Wireline Voice Services include local and long distance wireline services. Mobile Voice Services include local calls, domestic and international long distance calls and roaming services.
