China Telecom Corp Ltd (NYSE:CHA) Upgraded at Zacks Investment Research

		Posted by James Conley on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 



Tweet










China Telecom Corp Ltd (NYSE:CHA) was upgraded by Zacks Investment Research from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating in a report released on Tuesday, June 27th. The firm currently has a $54.00 price target on the utilities provider’s stock. Zacks Investment Research‘s price objective would indicate a potential upside of 12.73% from the company’s current price. 
According to Zacks, “China Telecom Corporation is a state-owned telecommunications company in China. They operate local telephone networks in ten provinces in China. They operate domestic and international fixed-line networks and infrastructure including wireless local loop, as well as telecom network-based voice, data, video, multimedia and information services.  They are also engaged in international telecom service settlement and expand into overseas markets.   “


 Get China Telecom Corp Ltd alerts:



Separately, BidaskClub downgraded China Telecom Corp from a “sell” rating to a “strong sell” rating in a report on Thursday, June 22nd. One equities research analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating, six have issued  a buy rating and one  has issued  a strong buy rating to the stock. The company presently has an average rating of “Buy” and an average price target of $54.00.




Shares of China Telecom Corp (NYSE CHA) opened at 47.90 on Tuesday. The company has a market cap of $38.77 billion, a P/E ratio of 14.52 and a beta of 0.66. The stock’s 50 day moving average is $48.26 and its 200-day moving average is $48.35. China Telecom Corp has a one year low of $45.58 and a one year high of $53.87. 
