anding Number of shares that are currently held by investors, including restricted shares owned by the company's officers and insiders as well as those held by the public. Public Float The number of shares in the hands of public investors and available to trade. To calculate, start with total shares outstanding and subtract the number of restricted shares. Restricted stock typically is that issued to company insiders with limits on when it may be traded. Dividend Yield A company's dividend expressed as a percentage of its current stock price.      Key Stock Data    P/E Ratio (TTM)  14.97 (07/21/17)      EPS (TTM)  $3.23      Market Cap $38.86 B     Shares Outstanding 138.77 M     Public Float N/A     Yield 2.80% (07/21/17)      Latest Dividend $1.351212 (07/31/17)      Ex-Dividend Date 05/24/17       ?    Shares Sold Short The total number of shares of a security that have been sold short and not yet repurchased. Change from Last Percentage change in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (06/30/17)    Shares Sold Short 66,466     Change from Last  -36.08%      Percent of Float N/A       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 2    1.09      Net Money Flow ($)  25,876    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors CHA      Company Change P/E (TTM)    CHU China Unicom (Hong Kong) Ltd. ADR   +1.99% +0.29   231.26     CHL China Mobile Ltd. ADR   +2.73% +1.44   13.55     HKTVY Hong Kong Television Network Ltd. ADR   -0.54% -0.04   -        More information on CHA   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile CHA      China Telecom Corp. Ltd. is engaged in the provision of wireline and mobile telecommunications services. Its products and services include wireline and mobile voice, internet, managed data and leased line, and integrated information application and other value-added...      31 Jinrong Street Beijing Beijing 100033 China   Email Website Map       Employees  287,076    Sector  Wired Telecommunications Services      Sales or Revenue  411.62 B    Industry  Telecommunication Services      1Y Sales Change  0.76%    Fiscal Year Ends December 31 Download Reports          Yi Xun Sui Chairman-Supervisory Board       Jie Yang Chairman & Chief Executive Officer       An Di Wu Chief Financial Officer & EVP       Jian Bin Zhang Member-Supervisory Board        More             Research & Ratings China Telecom Corp. Ltd. ADRCHA Per-Share Earnings, Actuals and Estimates      Quarterly   Annual    CHA will report FY 2017 earnings on false   CHA will report Q2 earnings on 08/23/2017         Actual     Analyst Range     Consensus      1.50  1.00  0.50  0.00           1.16        0.96        0.07        0.87       N/A     N/A     Q22016 Q3 Q4 Q12017  Q2 Q3          6.00  4.00  2.00  0.00          3.32        3.60        3.93        4.27       FY 2016 FY 2017 FY 2018 FY 2019              Q2 2017 Estimate Trends     Current: $-   1 month ago: $1.31   3 months ago: $1.31       Q3 2017 Estimate Trends     Current: $-   1 month ago: $1.16   3 months ago: $1.16         FY 2017 Estimate Trends     Current: $3.60   1 month ago: $3.60   3 months ago: $3.48       FY 2018 Estimate Trends     Current: $3.9